- I prefer bright, hook-driven 1960s pop: catchy, upbeat singles with tight vocal harmonies, jangly guitars, concise arrangements, and crisp, radio-friendly production that invite singing along or light, energetic listening.
- I value CDs that sequence memorable tracks for replay, emphasize melody and concise songcraft, and capture a nostalgic, feel‑good vibe.
